rComments: He is not as bad as many ppl said to me. Always willing to help. Hws, however, can be a real pain. In general, this class will cost you a decent chunk of time.

His lectures can be boring, but the modeling labs were actually pretty fun.  TIp of advice: Start the design project ASAP. Spent WAY too much time on that project for a 3 hr class. Its most of the grade since there's no final. What may seem like irrelevant info in lectures may end up showing up on exams. This class wasn't too bad and Leake is OK.

Not very relevant for CEE majors, though currently a requirement. A lot of hours a week required for only 3 credit hours. Boring lectures, but attendance is always taken. His book is practically his powerpoints, so you don't get many other views on subject matter. Should really be more than 3 credit hours.

Horrible exams.  Irrelevent assignments.  Boring lectures.  The final project was the biggest waste of time I've ever done.  I learned more about drawing on CADD in one week as an intern than in this whole class.

Pretty easy class. The modeling assignments aren't that bad, and sketching really isn't bad either. Just make sure to study the sketching theory before the written exams. As for the design project -- START EARLY. If you don't, you'll spend entire nights rendering images in the lab, which isn't fun -- trust me, I've done it.
He might be boring but you can tell he really knows his stuff. He is getting old but the class is still alright.
Cool guy. not too exciting early on but a good class.
He is just a jerk.
Sure, some of the class material, such as inventor assignments are fun. But, it seems Leake tries his hardest to make the class as boring as possible.

He can be very boring in lectures, but he's a nice guy willing to help. Inventor assignments are interesting and exams fair in content. Written exams test vocabulary and theory and can be tricky, but if you read the book and the lectures notes beforehand you won't have any problems.

He is a super nice person and knows his stuff! Even though it is a little boring in his lecture, if you are truly passionate about engineering you will be able to pay attention. I personally loved the class with all the work it required!
VERY boring lecture.  Tough class which requires a lot of work.

The class really isn't that hard if you play around with the programs enough.  Lecture is extremely boring.  Tests ask a lot of vocab and things that don't really matter but if you go over the lecture slides beforehand, you should do alright.  Be prepared to learn a lot on your own outside of class.

incredibly boring. he didn't seem very intelligent- i cannot fathom how he wrote a book on Inventor...he also assigned projects that weren't meant to be designed on Inventor (e.g. an entire airport). additionally, he made the assumption that everyone had taken a CAD class in high school, and completely left 1/3 of the class in the dust

Very dry. Hard to stay attentive during lectures, where he does take attendance. He doesn't communicate with his TAs, so it's difficult to know what to expect. On our first test he told us the day of, "we haven't gone over this at all, but there will be questions on it."
Easy, easy class if you are good at 3D visualization and modeling. Lecture is not entirely helpful. Professor is okay; neither fun nor bad.
Monotonous voice, pointless class, completely unhelpful, finds his class to be far superior than others
This guy is the definitioin of boring.  Accomplishes little in class and the test are irrelevant.  He needs to to revise the course.  Probably hasnt done that since the 90s.
Very monotone
this guy is a moron.  go get a life and stop playing with autodesk inventor for fun.
